Then in your client (batch job or whatever it happens to be), you can specify an autowired field for the `JavaMailSender`:

    @Autowired
    private JavaMailSender mailSender;

And then it would just be a case of creating and sending the message:

    SimpleMailMessage message = new SimpleMailMessage();
    message.setTo(to);
    message.setSubject(subject);
    message.setText(body); // Your aggregated messages
    mailSender.send(message);

That&#39;s the basics - but you&#39;ll find plenty of other articles and documentation discussing it in more detail around the web.


  [1]: http://springtips.blogspot.co.uk/2008/06/send-e-mail-using-spring-and-javamail.html

